crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The script first changes the current directory to `C:\Intel\`. It then executes the `ping` command, pausing execution for a short period. The script then uses `curl.exe` multiple times to download several files from `http://downdown.ru/` and save them into the `C:\Intel\` directory, including `driver.exe`, `blat.exe`, `svchost.exe`, `Trays.rar`, `C:\Intel\AnyDesk\wol.ps1`, and `dc.exe`. It also downloads `bat.bat` and saves it to `C:\Intel\AnyDesk`. `driver.exe` is then used to extract the contents of `Trays.rar` to the `C:\Intel\` directory, overwriting existing files without prompting. A shortcut file named `Trays.lnk` located inside the `C:\Intel\Trays` directory is then executed. Afterward, `svchost.exe` is executed with the `--install` flag and `C:\Intel\AnyDesk` as an argument. Finally, a shortcut file `C:\Intel\AnyDesk\bat.lnk` is executed.
